<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-06-25T14:45:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-06-25T14:45:00-05:00" n="646" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d646">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/2606: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Jefferson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-06-25T14:00:00-05:45"><hi rend="italic">June 25,
                                        1919, 2 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received
                                    June 26, 3.11 a.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Referring to my cable of June 9th, 11 a.m. Mr. Canton within the next 10
                            days expects to arrive at Bluefields to assume duties.</p>
                        <p>Now that matters have been placed in his hands, I do not believe that
                            there will be any difficulty in the prompt and satisfactory settlement
                            of the pending question including expulsion decree.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Jefferson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>